[{"id":"VR184688","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR184686.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The net charge on sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> after the wire is removed is</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR184688_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of two conducting spheres, labeled X and Y respectively. Sphere X has radius r and carries a positive Q charge. Sphere Y has radius 2 r and carries a positive Q charge. A note indicates that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" height=\"183\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR184686.g03.png\" width=\"250\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\">The two conducting spheres shown above each initially have a net positive charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>r</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 r\"><math alttext=\"2 r\" overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The two spheres are held fixed at a separation much greater than their radii. A conducting wire is now used to connect the two spheres. After any resulting current flow has ceased, the wire is removed.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive one third Q\"><math alttext=\"positive one third Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive one half Q\"><math alttext=\"positive one half Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive two thirds Q\"><math alttext=\"positive two thirds Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive three halves Q\"><math alttext=\"positive three halves Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]